Never used Yoga before but my best guess from the error would be that it&#39;s trying to increment uninitialised memory, based on **layoutMarkerData** appearing to be an instance of [Layout Data][1]:

    struct LayoutData {
        int layouts;
        int measures;
        int maxMeasureCache;
        int cachedLayouts;
        int cachedMeasures;
        int measureCallbacks;
        std::array&lt;int, static_cast&lt;uint8_t&gt;(LayoutPassReason::COUNT)&gt;
        measureCallbackReasonsCount;
    };
**cachedLayouts** and **cachedLayouts** are both ints that aren&#39;t given a default value so if LayoutData is [default initialised][2] they have the value of whatever was in memory a.k.a garbage.

So I would guess the fix is to assign them a value before the line you&#39;ve supplied.


  [1]: https://github.com/facebook/yoga/blob/90cded3819bb9849d0cfeaab05e811bfe6645c1c/yoga/event/event.h#L39
  [2]: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/default_initialization

