To capture the error message (and verify if it exists or not), you can implement the following--

First, a `DoesElementExist` method which checks for the presence of a WebElement, and returns `true` or `false` based on element&#39;s existence:

````
public static bool DoesElementExist(this AndroidDriver&lt;AppiumWebElement&gt; driver, By locator)
{
    // attempt to locate element
    try
    {
        // return true if found
        return Driver.FindElements(locator).Count &gt; 0;
    }
    catch (NoSuchElementException)
    {
        // if we catch exception, element does not exist, return false
        return false
    }
}

````

We can call our method to check the error message as such:

````
bool doesErrorMessageExist = driver.DoesElementExist(By.XPath(&quot;//*[contains(@text, &#39;Invalid number&#39;)]&quot;);
````

This will return true if the error message appears on the page, and false if it does not.

