You are using  `Sequence.requests` which is typed as `BaseRequest[]`, so if you want to preserve the type you would need to make `Sequence` generic as well.

e.g.

```typescript
class Sequence&lt;T extends BaseRequest&gt; {
  requests: T[];

  add(request: T) {
    this.requests.push(request);
  }

  merge(sequence: Sequence&lt;T&gt;) {
    this.requests = this.requests.concat(sequence.requests);
  }
}
```

```typescript
let request = RequestBuilder(params);
let sequence = new Sequence&lt;CreateJobRequest&gt;();
sequence.requests.push(request);
```

Note that this would also affect the typing of `merge`, because you cannot merge just any array of requests.

